1st LD: Somali pirates hijack Saudi Arabian-owned oil tanker NAIROBI, Nov. 17 -- Somali pirates have hijacked a Saudi Arabian-owned oil tanker, the largest vessel ever seized, loaded with crude and carrying 25 crew members off the Kenyan coast, a regional maritime official said on Monday.
Saturday's hijacking of the MV Sirius Star tanker occurred in the Indian Ocean far south of the zone patrolled by international warships in the busy Gulf of Aden shipping channel, which leads to and from the Suez Canal.
Reports from the U.S. Navy said the tanker, Sirius Star, operated by Vela International, was hijacked.
